parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Plural
str2: To step in; I go onboard a ship, embark. From en and the base of basis; to walk on, i.e. Embark, reach.
A ship, vessel, boat. From pleo; a sailer, i.e. Vessel.

parse: Verb - Imperfect Indicative Middle or Passive - 3rd Person Plural

str2: Over, on the other side, beyond. Apparently accusative case of an obsolete derivative of peiro; through, i.e. Across.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Probably prolonged from hals; the sea.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
Capernaum, a town of Galilee. Of Hebrew origin; Capernaum, a place in Palestine.

parse: Verb - Pluperfect Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: A prolongation and middle voice form of a primary verb; to cause to be, i.e. to become, used with great latitude.
Already; now at length, now after all this waiting. Apparently from e and de; even now.
Darkness; fig: spiritual darkness. From skotos; dimness, obscurity.
Of Hebrew origin; Jesus, the name of our Lord and two other Israelites.

parse: Verb - Pluperfect Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular

str2: To, towards, with. A strengthened form of pro; a preposition of direction; forward to, i.e. Toward.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Accusative Masculine 3rd Person Plural
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
